# Cursor rules — liminal-prototype

You are working in liminal-prototype, the public demo surface + design-system reference for Liminal.

## Read first (the shared brain)
- `CLAUDE.md` in this repo — points to the canonical context.
- `~/liminal/founder-brain/meta/SHARED_CONTEXT.md` — single source of truth for bio, brand, voice, banned words, core sentence. Honor it. (Present on the maintainer's machine.)

## Hard rules (non-negotiable)
- Brand name is "Liminal" — ONE word, never "Liminal Space" (the domain is a URL artifact only).
- Core sentence: "Liminal gives form to inner life."
- Founder bio: Shruti did NOT attend Stanford / NO Stanford GSB MBA / NOT a South Park Commons member. UC Berkeley (CogSci + CS); ex-PM Asana/Cloudflare/Robinhood/Ancestry; co-founder Sean Nejad.
- Banned words: transformation, journey, companion, unlock, manifest, healing, optimize, breakthrough, flourishing, wellness, emotional intelligence, empathic.
- No em dashes in external copy. No emojis on external surfaces.
- NOT a wellness app, coaching tool, AI companion, mood tracker, meditation app, or HR platform.

## This repo (local)
- Public demo cuts (`cuts/*.html`) + `index.html`. Live at liminalshruti.github.io/liminal-prototype/.
- This repo holds the canonical `design-tokens.css` (the practical token upstream). When styling, consume the canonical tokens — do not inline hardcoded colors/type.
- Type stack: Nineties Headliner + Perfectly Nineties + Geist Mono. No Inter/Helvetica/system-ui as primary.
- This is a PUBLIC surface — bio/brand hard-stops and claim-veracity are load-bearing.
